reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I'm not sure how I lost my old one - but I'm glad this was available
reviews.reviewText: It is unclear to me how it is really possible that I misplaced the power cord to our TV set. Yes, it was unplugged for a while, but it was not moved more than a couple of feet. Yet, when I went to put everything in the room back to its original location, the cord was nowhere to be found.Our TV is a no-name brand and I couldn't find it listed anywhere. Looking at the place it plugs into the TV and at this cord, they seemed to be the same - and I took the chance. It worked out well. I'm not really sure what else to say. It's a power cord. It did the job - and there were no detectable defects. It does what it is supposed to.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars When you need it, you need it
reviews.reviewText: So, I have a wall mounted tv, with a cable channel that is 6 feet long, and every single cable that comes with a tv for some bizarre reason is 5 feet long.So, get a 10 foot cable, and... for me I have shortened it to 6 feet by simply cutting it and wiring in a different plug.But, yeah, when you need that slightly longer cable, you just need it, and this did it. Great job.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 10 Foot Long Power Cord With Special Plug For Some TVs and Other Devices
reviews.reviewText: This works well for what it is intended to be for. A 10ft long power cord with the special plug for some TVs and other electronic devices. It is rated at 10 amps, and for most things, this will do just fine. Sometimes the outlet is not where you need it to be, and instead of having to run another extension cord, this will most likely reach where you need it to go. Price was a fair price at the time of this review.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This was bought to be used with my projector, It came with a 3 foot power cord and it was impossible to mount it where I needed, this cable fixed my issue, gave me plenty of room to move it and place it where I needed, worked with no issue and snapped into the back of the projector like it came with it,

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No more extension cord needed for my monitor
reviews.reviewText: The way I have my home office set up, I have to use an extension cord to power my 2nd monitor since the outlet is out of reach. This 10ft. power cord is exactly what I needed to eliminate the extension cord once and for all! It's a perfect match for the Samsung power transformer and about twice as long as the cord that came with my monitor. I never knew a longer cord existed, but I'm certainly glad I found one on Amazon.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lightweight and Works Well
reviews.reviewText: I needed a longer power cord for my laptop adapter. This one is listed as being for a TV, but the socket is the same.The cord itself is relatively thin, but it's rated to carry 10A. My power supply pulls only ~2.5A.So it works well, doesn't get warm, and is more than long enough. This should work fine with any modern TV, or any device that draws under 10A and uses a similar socket.
